2.1  Cross Section Evaluation Procedure                           4043 1451
---------------------------------------                           4043 1451
                                                                  4043 1451
   Because the Zr isotopes are so close to a closed shell, the    4043 1451
total and elastic cross sections exhibit pronounced fluctuations  4043 1451
up to nearly 1 MeV. To preserve these fluctuations, which were    4043 1451
present in the original ENDF/B-VII.8 evaluation and integral      4043 1451
testing suggests are important, we used EMPIRE's ability to tune  4043 1451
cross sections to data to match natZr(n,tot). Total cross         4043 1451
sections in all of the Zr isotopes were abundance weighted to     4043 1451
sum up to natZr(n,tot) while elastic cross sections were          4043 1451
obtained subtracting non-elastic channels from the total. Whilst  4043 1451
strictly speaking this is not correct, it preserves the           4043 1451
transport cross section for natZr while leaving the activation    4043 1451
cross sections for the individual isotopes unchanged.             4043 1451
                                                                  4043 1451
                                                                  4043 1451
2.2  Elastic Channel Modifications                                4043 1451
----------------------------------                                4043 1451
                                                                  4043 1451
   Extensive comparison of the calculated elastic angular         4043 1451
distributions with the wealthy amount of experimental data        4043 1451
(about 150 plots in all) demonstrated that JENDL-4.0 using the    4043 1451
Walter-Guss OMP below 6 MeV, and Koning-Deleroche OMP above 6     4043 1451
MeV describes measurements better, especially at low incident     4043 1451
energies. Since KAPL sensitivity studies indicated that elastic   4043 1451
angular distributions might be of importance for their integral   4043 1451
testing we adopted the (n,el) angular distributions from          4043 1451
JENDL-4.0 [3]. Our tuning of the elastic cross sections slightly  4043 1451
improves agreement with the experimental data. Benchmarking       4043 1451
performed with the suite of 22 integral experiments (see          4043 1451
ENDF/B-VII.1 validation paper) confirmed that switching to the    4043 1451
JENDL angular distributions reduces over prediction of the TRIGA  4043 1451
132 and 133 reactivities by 50% bringing our results well within  4043 1451
the experimental uncertainties.                                   4043 1451
