4  Covariance Data                                                4043 1451
==================                                                4043 1451
                                                                  4043 1451
   The covariance data was taken from the 96Zr evalaution in the  4043 1451
COMMARA-2.0 library [5].                                          4043 1451
  In thermal and resolved resonance region we made use of the     4043 1451
covariance formalism based on the kernel approximation along      4043 1451
with data in the Atlas of Neutron Resonances.                     4043 1451
  In fast neutron region up to 20 MeV covariance estimates were   4043 1451
calculated using the nuclear reaction code EMPIRE and the         4043 1451
Bayesian code KALMAN. The KALMAN code along with selected         4043 1451
experimental data was used to determine the correlation matrix    4043 1451
of the model parameters. Furthermore, additional parameters       4043 1451
scaling total and absorption cross sections were included to      4043 1451
prevent the unrealistic drop in the cross-section uncertainties   4043 1451
and, in some instance, to cover the spread of the experimental    4043 1451
data. The total cross-section uncertainties were computed as the  4043 1451
sum of elastic, inelastic, (n2n), and capture.                    4043 1451
